<img class="aligncenter wp-image-1247399" src="https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Ebola.jpg?resize=500%2C295&#038;ssl=1" alt="Rwanda starts Ebola vaccination campaign" width="500" height="295" srcset="https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Ebola.jpg?resize=1024%2C605&amp;ssl=1 1024w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Ebola.jpg?resize=300%2C177&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Ebola.jpg?resize=768%2C454&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Ebola.jpg?resize=58%2C34&amp;ssl=1 58w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Ebola.jpg?resize=260%2C154&amp;ssl=1 260w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Ebola.jpg?resize=200%2C118&amp;ssl=1 200w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Ebola.jpg?resize=560%2C331&amp;ssl=1 560w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Ebola.jpg?w=1500&amp;ssl=1 1500w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Ebola.jpg?w=1280&amp;ssl=1 1280w" sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" data-recalc-dims="1" /> Rwanda has launched its first large-scale vaccination campaign against the Ebola virus. At least 200,000 people will be vaccinated over the next year in areas bordering the Democratic Republic of Congo, Rwanda’s health minister Diane Gashumba said at the weekend. Priority will be given to health workers, immigration officials, police and those engaged in cross-border trade. So far there have been no confirmed Ebola cases in Rwanda. The authorities are hoping the experimental vaccine will keep things that way. More than 2,200 people have died from the disease in neighbouring DR Congo since August last year. The vaccine was used for the first time last month in the city of Goma in eastern DR Congo. A quarter of a million Congolese have already been vaccinated with another product – both are made by US drug companies. vanguard Medical workers in Democratic Republic of Congo(DRC) on Tuesday concluded vaccination of Ebola patients in the city of Mbandaka with experimental vaccine, the health ministry said. June 5, 2018 In "News" Authorities in the Democratic Republic of Congo are planning to use a second Ebola vaccine to help control an outbreak that has killed more than 2,100 people. In July, former Health Minister Oly Ilunga opposed its use saying it had not been proved effective. But DR Congo health officials say… September 22, 2019 In "Health" The head of the World Health Organization said Sunday there has been another reported case of Ebola in the Democratic Republic of Congo and that an experimental vaccine to fight the disease is expected to become available in the country this week. May 14, 2018 In "Health"